      <mj-section>
        <mj-column>
          <!-- Dash &#8209; -->
          <mj-text>
            <h3>Update from Miles Stock, Vice Chair Yavneh</h3>
            <p>As the winter months fade into memory and the evenings begin to stretch a little longer, this feels like a natural moment to pause and reflect. The past few months have been full and joyful, marked by many simchas and by meaningful gatherings for Tu Bishvat, Purim and Pesach. At the same time, we are already looking ahead to what the coming months will bring — from next week’s sold out BES Community Lunch, to our plans for the days and evenings of Shavuot, and (dare I say it) even the High Holy Days. For some, the date most eagerly anticipated is the AGM on 13 May, when several of our community members will be recognised through the awarding of the BESties 2026.</p>
            <p> With the AGM in mind, I would like to take this opportunity to thank all members of our Shul Council for the commitment, time and energy they give so generously on behalf of the community. This year, the Senior Leadership Team has introduced a set of portfolios to allow council members to support BES in a more focused and effective way, and I very much look forward to working together over the coming 12 months.</p>
            <p> This Shabbat is a particularly special one, as we welcome Mizrachi Weekend of Inspiration. We began with a memorable evening during the week, hearing Rabbi Doron Perez in conversation with Eddie Hammerman, and we are delighted to be hosting Rabbanit Karen Hochhauser and Rabbi Anthony Manning, who will each be speaking at both sites over Shabbat. I very much encourage you to try to hear them if you can.</p>
            <p> Finally, for those with an eye on our community’s history, April 2007 marked the first Yavneh minyan. This week therefore begins our <em>“BES@Yavneh at 20”</em> celebrations — with several exciting plans already in the works, which I look forward to sharing in due course.</p>
            <p> Wishing you all a warm Shabbat Shalom, and an enjoyable extra long weekend. <br /> Miles Stock<br />Vice Chair Yavneh </p>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-image src="https://borehamwoodshul.org/assets/uploads/2026/05/woi-2026.png" />
          <mj-spacer />
      </mj-section>
